1. Java 21 Virtual Threads — Not in Our Plan Yet (High Value)
Enterprise-Architecture-Decision.md specifically calls out Java 21 Virtual Threads (Project Loom) as the reason modern Spring Boot matches Node.js concurrency. We listed Java 21 as the version but never mentioned this.

Why it matters for the POC: It directly answers the evaluator's implicit question "can Spring Boot handle 200M customer scale?" — and the answer is yes, because Virtual Threads let a single Spring Boot instance handle millions of concurrent connections without reactive programming complexity.

Add to our plan: Enable Virtual Threads in application.yml:

spring:
  threads:
    virtual:
      enabled: true
One line. Huge justification value.